Sequence Information.Peptide Name: B34 (natural AMPs-like, cattle, ruminant, mammals; animals; UCLL1)
Sequence Information.Source: Bos taurus; a 34-residue fragment from beef hydrosate obtained via enzyme digestion and isolation,

Literature.Author: Maky MA, Zendo T. 2021
Literature.Title: Generation and Characterization of Novel Bioactive Peptides from Fish and Beef Hydrolysates

Sequence Information.Comments: Discovery: a natural fragment isolated from enzyme digestion of beef.Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (40%) toTemporin-MS1.Activity: Active against E.faecalis JCM 5803T (MIC >184ug/ml), L.innocua ATCC 33090T (MIC >184 ug/ml), E.coli JM109 (MIC >184 ug/ml), B.coagulans CM 2257 (MIC >184 ug/ml), P.putida ATCC 12633 (MIC >184 ug/ml), S.enterica subsp. enterica NBRC 13245 (MIC >184 ug/ml), and P. vulgaris F24B (MIC 24 uM or 91.6 ug/ml).APD note: "Like" means "its existence in vivo to be confirmed".
